00:54:55.330 --> 00:54:56.557
He's in the middle of the stage

00:54:56.557 --> 00:54:58.520
and they start the intro
to "Polk Salad Annie"

00:54:58.520 --> 00:55:01.123
and he comes over to me
and he goes, Rockin' Robin.

00:55:10.059 --> 00:55:14.559
("Polk Salad Annie" by Elvis Presley)

00:55:24.915 --> 00:55:26.915
- [Elvis] Rockin' Robin.

00:55:28.360 --> 00:55:30.000
- I still get chills when I hear that,

00:55:30.000 --> 00:55:31.600
I still get chills when I know

00:55:31.600 --> 00:55:35.067
that he walked over and
went, Rockin' Robin.

00:55:36.160 --> 00:55:37.860
- Just grab hold, honey, anywhere.

00:55:38.749 --> 00:55:40.328
There you go.

00:55:40.328 --> 00:55:42.495
Hi, you wanna get serious
or just wait a little bit?

00:55:42.495 --> 00:55:43.420
- [Fan] Yes!

00:55:43.420 --> 00:55:46.354
(audience laughs)

00:55:46.354 --> 00:55:48.521
- Whoa, whatsamatter baby?

00:55:50.034 --> 00:55:51.868
(fan sobbing and laughing)

00:55:51.868 --> 00:55:53.360
(audience laughs)

00:55:53.360 --> 00:55:54.960
- [Annie] To be kissed by Elvis.

00:55:57.146 --> 00:55:58.729
- [Fan] I love you!

00:56:00.451 --> 00:56:03.284
- [Annie] Would it feel like this?

00:56:12.310 --> 00:56:13.620
While scrubbing through my archive,

00:56:13.620 --> 00:56:15.973
I happened upon a few unnumbered tapes.

00:56:16.910 --> 00:56:20.008
Rare moments when I wasn't
thinking about the film.

00:56:20.008 --> 00:56:22.591
(somber music)

00:56:24.390 --> 00:56:25.440
My brother's wedding.

00:56:27.200 --> 00:56:30.853
Matt, my love, who'd come on
every shoot, now shooting me.

00:56:33.070 --> 00:56:36.603
and Nora, she came all
the way from Iceland.

00:56:39.720 --> 00:56:41.023
The dance of time.

00:56:42.611 --> 00:56:44.611
A miraculous loop I can play infinitely.

00:56:57.320 --> 00:56:58.990
I'm losing count of how many memorials

00:56:58.990 --> 00:57:00.843
and Easters there have been.

00:57:04.130 --> 00:57:05.963
Miscellaneous tape 34,

00:57:06.930 --> 00:57:09.230
where I can no longer
ignore my own obsession.

00:57:10.770 --> 00:57:11.903
I'm 33 now.

00:57:14.740 --> 00:57:15.750
My fiancee Matt

00:57:15.750 --> 00:57:19.360
who was there from the very
start of this film, leaves.

00:57:19.360 --> 00:57:22.608
And my mom thinks I should
get professional help.

00:57:22.608 --> 00:57:25.450
(soft music)

00:57:25.450 --> 00:57:27.350
I end up on this couch

00:57:27.350 --> 00:57:29.800
talking more about the
film than my relationship.

00:57:34.170 --> 00:57:38.223
My analyst tells me a story
of a patient, a hoarder.

00:57:39.429 --> 00:57:41.090
He tells me that when
you're no longer able

00:57:41.090 --> 00:57:44.573
to tell what's relevant,
everything becomes significant.

00:57:50.260 --> 00:57:53.140
I asked if he thought I was losing my way,

00:57:53.140 --> 00:57:55.790
but he's not in the business
of answering questions,

00:57:55.790 --> 00:57:56.973
only posing more.

00:58:00.120 --> 00:58:03.050
I did what I do to make sense of my world.

00:58:03.050 --> 00:58:04.213
I continued shooting,

00:58:05.230 --> 00:58:08.023
joining 800,000 on their
pilgrimage to see the Pope.

00:58:10.330 --> 00:58:13.593
Pope tape 43, World Youth Day, Toronto.

00:58:15.297 --> 00:58:19.214
(fans cheering and chattering)

00:58:20.760 --> 00:58:22.610
Why did i think this was a good idea?

00:58:27.500 --> 00:58:29.180
I tried to imagine the one image

00:58:29.180 --> 00:58:32.223
that might make this all
worth it, and I couldn't.

00:58:33.340 --> 00:58:37.763
Still, I kept shooting, bearing my cross.

00:58:39.245 --> 00:58:42.380
(rock music)

00:58:42.380 --> 00:58:43.600
The Pope created this event

00:58:43.600 --> 00:58:45.400
to unite the youth around the world.

00:58:46.789 --> 00:58:49.660
500,000 now fill this airfield,

00:58:49.660 --> 00:58:51.610
for what we sense will be his last one.

00:58:53.807 --> 00:58:57.557
(fans clapping and cheering)

00:59:03.680 --> 00:59:06.863
A newspaper called it 'Popestock',
the Catholic Woodstock.

00:59:07.920 --> 00:59:08.920
And I could see why.

00:59:13.360 --> 00:59:14.280
Pope tape 44.

00:59:14.280 --> 00:59:18.200
- I think the Pope is coming
again to do mass in the morning

00:59:18.200 --> 00:59:20.860
and hopefully we'll get to see him.

00:59:20.860 --> 00:59:23.090
I think to night we're
definitely not gonna sleep,

00:59:23.090 --> 00:59:25.240
we're gonna be up all night praying

00:59:25.240 --> 00:59:28.986
and singing with other groups,
getting to know other groups,

00:59:28.986 --> 00:59:29.980
we'll definitely not sleep.

00:59:29.980 --> 00:59:32.819
It will just be a big celebration.

00:59:32.819 --> 00:59:35.443
(uplifting music)

00:59:35.443 --> 00:59:36.763
- [Annie] Pope tape 45.

00:59:38.141 --> 00:59:42.058
(audience cheers and applauds)

00:59:53.810 --> 00:59:54.793
Pope tape 46.

00:59:56.280 --> 00:59:59.000
Last night, while I found
shelter in the media center,

00:59:59.000 --> 01:00:00.190
this youth group from Boston

01:00:00.190 --> 01:00:02.073
camped outside in the rain and mud.

01:00:04.760 --> 01:00:06.350
- Right now we're waiting for the pope

01:00:06.350 --> 01:00:08.410
and we're not sure if he's coming by.

01:00:08.410 --> 01:00:10.400
A lot of us are really
frustrated and tired

01:00:10.400 --> 01:00:11.680
'cause we didn't get a lot of sleep

01:00:11.680 --> 01:00:16.500
and we're just kinda waiting
to see if he'll show or.

01:00:16.500 --> 01:00:19.740
And these are all these people
behind us blocked our view.

01:00:19.740 --> 01:00:22.190
And so everyone's kinda
really annoyed right now.

01:00:23.137 --> 01:00:24.979
- It's still really fun going.
- Yeah.

01:00:24.979 --> 01:00:28.610
- Even though we're all soaking
wet and tired and stuff,

01:00:28.610 --> 01:00:31.103
it's still gonna be awesome
no matter what happens.

01:00:34.900 --> 01:00:36.050
- [Annie] Pope tape 47.

01:00:38.643 --> 01:00:41.560
(crowd chattering)

01:00:48.979 --> 01:00:52.896
(fans cheering and applauding)

01:02:01.993 --> 01:02:05.910
(audience cheers and applauds)

01:02:23.920 --> 01:02:27.330
- [Annie] We left, filthy and exhausted,

01:02:27.330 --> 01:02:29.223
each bearing our own cross.

01:02:30.410 --> 01:02:33.833
but each in our own ways
feeling it was worth it.

01:02:35.094 --> 01:02:37.927
(uplifting music)

01:02:45.960 --> 01:02:47.103
Super 8 reel five.

01:02:48.370 --> 01:02:50.750
This Elvis Week, I finally
made the pilgrimage

01:02:50.750 --> 01:02:53.263
to Elvis's birthplace
in Tupelo, Mississippi.

01:02:54.500 --> 01:02:58.363
The shotgun shack his father
built, the humble beginnings.

01:02:59.620 --> 01:03:02.200
I met his old neighbor, Mrs. MacComb.

01:03:02.200 --> 01:03:05.280
She told me Elvis didn't have a halo.

01:03:05.280 --> 01:03:07.900
- [Mrs. MacComb] He was just
Vernon and Gladys's kid.

01:03:07.900 --> 01:03:11.320
And he was not a big deal.

01:03:11.320 --> 01:03:13.850
But we kept up, I knew all the relatives.

01:03:13.850 --> 01:03:15.740
- [Annie] The kid next door.

01:03:15.740 --> 01:03:18.483
Hard to imagine now,
that he's cast in bronze.

01:03:24.880 --> 01:03:26.113
Elvis tape 33.

01:03:27.860 --> 01:03:30.320
It was Joe's first time to Tupelo also,

01:03:30.320 --> 01:03:33.063
though he comes every year
to Graceland for Elvis Week.

01:03:34.080 --> 01:03:36.490
His first trip was with his own father,

01:03:36.490 --> 01:03:38.630
and now he brings his son, Kyle,

01:03:38.630 --> 01:03:41.480
who he hopes will carry on
this family tradition one day.

01:03:46.390 --> 01:03:50.070
When I ask him why he is a
fan, he squirms and says,

01:03:50.070 --> 01:03:51.420
because my dad is.

01:03:51.420 --> 01:03:54.073
and He likes Elvis so much, and so do I.

01:03:57.050 --> 01:04:00.683
He can't explain it, but
isn't that explanation enough?

01:04:06.310 --> 01:04:08.880
- Elvis was born here in this house,

01:04:08.880 --> 01:04:11.120
and because of that quirk of fate,

01:04:11.120 --> 01:04:13.580
Tupelo may become, if it isn't already,

01:04:13.580 --> 01:04:16.100
the Mecca for rock and roll fans.

01:04:16.100 --> 01:04:19.550
Janes Jones was two grades
behind Elvis in school.

01:04:19.550 --> 01:04:21.840
She said they were all dirt poor,

01:04:21.840 --> 01:04:25.710
maybe that's why when Elvis
made it big, truckloads of toys

01:04:25.710 --> 01:04:28.160
starting arriving in
Tupelo every Christmas

01:04:28.160 --> 01:04:29.780
for the town's needy kids.

01:04:29.780 --> 01:04:31.180
- Of course it was anonymously,

01:04:31.180 --> 01:04:33.550
but everybody knew who was sending it,

01:04:33.550 --> 01:04:37.140
it came from Memphis
so it had to be Elvis.

01:04:37.140 --> 01:04:39.233
- [Reporter] What has his
death meant to Tupelo?

01:04:40.510 --> 01:04:42.460
- Ain't no way we can say what we feel.

01:04:45.901 --> 01:04:46.734
Well, it's  . . .

01:04:48.433 --> 01:04:51.900
it's like your own family has died.

01:04:51.900 --> 01:04:53.900
- [Reporter] What did your daughter say?

01:04:53.900 --> 01:04:56.467
- She said, mama, it's
like God himself died.

01:04:59.130 --> 01:05:02.797
("Also Sprach Zarathustra")

01:05:17.890 --> 01:05:20.550
- [Annie] Images of the
King World Championship,

01:05:20.550 --> 01:05:23.093
The Holiday Inn, Memphis, Tennessee.

01:05:27.609 --> 01:05:30.192
(lively music)

01:05:34.140 --> 01:05:36.940
To be named the Ultimate
Image of the King,

01:05:36.940 --> 01:05:39.223
one must bring the crowd closer to Elvis.

01:05:40.330 --> 01:05:41.503
Elvis tape 95.

01:05:46.060 --> 01:05:49.240
I shot five tapes worth of
belt buckles, sideburns,

01:05:49.240 --> 01:05:52.203
gyrating hips, karate
moves, rings, and jumpsuits.

01:05:53.510 --> 01:05:54.910
I just couldn't help myself.

01:05:56.815 --> 01:05:59.860
(lively music)

01:05:59.860 --> 01:06:02.290
And found it unbelievable
that fans treasured

01:06:02.290 --> 01:06:04.800
the sweat doused scarves of impersonators,

01:06:04.800 --> 01:06:07.458
just as they had Elvis's.

01:06:07.458 --> 01:06:10.091
Look at this.

01:06:13.957 --> 01:06:18.948
♪ Glory, glory, hallelujah ♪

01:06:21.006 --> 01:06:22.266
- [Annie] I remember Elvis once saying

01:06:22.266 --> 01:06:24.276
that fans just wanted pieces of him

01:06:24.276 --> 01:06:25.881
for souvenirs, that's all.

01:06:27.967 --> 01:06:31.217
(impersonator singing)

01:06:32.170 --> 01:06:33.187
Maybe that's all.

01:06:36.338 --> 01:06:39.588
(impersonator singing "Teddy Bear")

01:06:48.488 --> 01:06:50.130
- Elvis!

01:06:50.130 --> 01:06:53.380
(impersonator singing)

01:06:58.228 --> 01:07:02.145
(audience cheers and applauds)

01:07:07.760 --> 01:07:09.170
- [Annie] It was backstage
where I discovered

01:07:09.170 --> 01:07:11.633
why this event is called
Images of the King.

01:07:12.720 --> 01:07:15.420
They can't even use Elvis's name,

01:07:15.420 --> 01:07:17.570
out of fear of being
pursued by his estate.

01:07:20.720 --> 01:07:23.703
And that's the craziest
thing of all, catch that?

01:07:24.610 --> 01:07:27.973
Some already have been sued, and for what?

01:07:29.210 --> 01:07:31.580
I learned they don't make
any money doing this.

01:07:31.580 --> 01:07:34.560
They just want to show the
world how great Elvis was,

01:07:34.560 --> 01:07:38.417
pass him on to the next
generation, like others I'd met.

01:07:41.030 --> 01:07:43.550
This guy tells me he never
really got the whole Elvis thing

01:07:43.550 --> 01:07:47.080
until he saw an impersonator
who made him wonder,

01:07:47.080 --> 01:07:48.703
was Elvis really this good?

01:07:53.460 --> 01:07:58.093
He looked into it and discovered,
Elvis was even better.

01:07:59.980 --> 01:08:01.880
He's been performing Elvis ever since.

01:08:05.860 --> 01:08:07.270
And it reminded me of the first time

01:08:07.270 --> 01:08:08.793
I fell in love with Elvis.

01:08:13.070 --> 01:08:15.453
In a book of Kata
Billups's Elvis paintings.

01:08:18.390 --> 01:08:20.053
Her Elvis is infinite.

01:08:23.810 --> 01:08:27.713
And one day, she invited me to
her studio in South Carolina.

01:08:29.956 --> 01:08:34.340
- This one is called "Jesus
Taught Elvis to Cook."

01:08:34.340 --> 01:08:35.540
- [Annie] Elvis tape 99.

01:08:37.030 --> 01:08:39.030
- [Kata] Which could've really happened.

01:08:39.030 --> 01:08:41.663
It's kind of a modern day mythology.

01:08:45.700 --> 01:08:48.970
This is called, "I Saw Elvis
on the Bumper Car Rides

01:08:48.970 --> 01:08:50.650
at the County Fair."

01:08:50.650 --> 01:08:51.700
- [Annie] Kata said that Graceland

01:08:51.700 --> 01:08:54.260
has a way of sanitizing his image,

01:08:54.260 --> 01:08:56.410
to a point where
everything looks the same.

01:08:57.547 --> 01:09:00.677
- "I Saw Elvis Working Shoe Land."

01:09:12.050 --> 01:09:16.670
This one is called 'I
Saw Elvis by the Roadside

01:09:16.670 --> 01:09:18.587
Selling Velvet Paintings."

01:09:19.660 --> 01:09:23.273
Susan Sarandon owns the
original painting of this.

01:09:35.500 --> 01:09:37.450
- [Annie] Off camera,
Kata revealed that she too

01:09:37.450 --> 01:09:40.240
had received a cease and desist letter,

01:09:40.240 --> 01:09:42.270
and it scared her enough
to stop showing her work

01:09:42.270 --> 01:09:43.573
for a couple years.

01:09:45.560 --> 01:09:46.800
But could it really be so wrong

01:09:46.800 --> 01:09:48.763
to interpret what Elvis means to you?

01:09:50.026 --> 01:09:51.292
- [Reporter] Are you satisfied

01:09:51.292 --> 01:09:52.569
with the image you've established?

01:09:52.569 --> 01:09:53.607
- Well, the image is one thing

01:09:53.607 --> 01:09:55.833
and the human being is another.

01:09:55.833 --> 01:09:57.659
- [Reporter] How close
is the image to the man?

01:09:57.659 --> 01:10:00.863
- [Annie] So, there's
something I'm not telling you.

01:10:01.700 --> 01:10:03.723
A subplot I've chosen to ignore.

01:10:05.400 --> 01:10:06.853
I'm not licensed either.

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:11.553
I keep going but always
with this lingering fear,

01:10:12.460 --> 01:10:14.833
could Elvis's estate shut me down?

01:10:21.760 --> 01:10:25.020
They say there can be only
one documentary about Elvis,

01:10:25.020 --> 01:10:30.020
their own, one musical, only
one official Vegas show,

01:10:31.650 --> 01:10:33.163
only one Elvis.

01:10:34.470 --> 01:10:36.980
Because they claim ownership of Elvis,

01:10:36.980 --> 01:10:40.713
his name, his image, his likeness.

01:10:45.340 --> 01:10:50.340
Name, image, and likeness,
what does that even mean?

01:10:53.840 --> 01:10:56.620
Because all these decades since his death,

01:10:56.620 --> 01:11:00.103
Elvis has become an image, an idea,

01:11:01.529 --> 01:11:03.513
that sits in each of our brains.

01:11:05.210 --> 01:11:07.373
Can't there be room for everyone's Elvis?

01:11:10.658 --> 01:11:13.075
(calm music)

01:11:21.410 --> 01:11:23.726
Elvis as America.

01:11:23.726 --> 01:11:25.351
As patriot.

01:11:25.351 --> 01:11:28.018
As companion.

01:11:28.018 --> 01:11:33.018
Elvis as French, and Elvis as Cowboy.

01:11:33.337 --> 01:11:35.170
As sweatered.

01:11:35.170 --> 01:11:37.252
As lover.

01:11:37.252 --> 01:11:39.452
As a life ring, as savior

01:11:40.452 --> 01:11:41.285
As saint.

01:11:43.570 --> 01:11:44.423
As martyred.

01:11:48.030 --> 01:11:52.735
Maybe our images of Elvis
say more about us than him.

01:11:54.010 --> 01:11:57.206
It's how we internalize Elvis.

01:12:00.610 --> 01:12:05.603
All three of my icons,
Elvis, the Pope, and Diana,

01:12:06.600 --> 01:12:07.763
have become ideas,

01:12:11.603 --> 01:12:14.519
part of the landscape.

01:12:36.150 --> 01:12:39.843
How can you own something
so big, so undefinable?

01:12:41.200 --> 01:12:43.037
So much a part of who we are?

01:12:46.550 --> 01:12:48.967
(door thuds)

01:12:54.080 --> 01:12:56.333
It's strange to think
of Elvis as property.

01:12:57.490 --> 01:13:02.123
Something that can be bought,
sold, controlled, removed.

01:13:08.526 --> 01:13:11.359
(thunder booming)

01:13:16.010 --> 01:13:17.603
I had a dream last night.

01:13:18.800 --> 01:13:19.903
A nightmare actually.

01:13:20.920 --> 01:13:23.020
I dreamt the Elvis police
came in the dead of night

01:13:23.020 --> 01:13:24.513
and seized all of the film.

01:13:28.610 --> 01:13:31.773
They returned, later,
dropping off the remains.

01:13:34.810 --> 01:13:36.763
Not a trace was left of Elvis.

01:13:39.050 --> 01:13:41.690
Panicked, I went to bury the remains

01:13:41.690 --> 01:13:43.233
in an undisclosed location.

01:13:45.264 --> 01:13:47.847
(somber music)

01:13:53.048 --> 01:13:55.310
But it wasn't enough for them.

01:13:55.310 --> 01:13:58.163
Bloodthirsty, they went after others too.

01:13:59.440 --> 01:14:02.683
Seizing original paintings,
drawings, t-shirts,

01:14:03.600 --> 01:14:06.140
and delivered the loot to Dracula himself.

01:14:07.264 --> 01:14:11.014
(moves to suspenseful music)

01:14:17.470 --> 01:14:19.543
- [Therapist] That must be unsettling

01:14:19.543 --> 01:14:21.890
after all the time you've invested in it.

01:14:21.890 --> 01:14:24.490
To think you might not be
able to complete the film.

01:14:25.510 --> 01:14:27.203
What do you think you're gonna do?

01:14:28.560 --> 01:14:33.560
(voice begins to echo)

01:14:38.330 --> 01:14:39.533
- [Annie] Pope tape 73.

01:14:42.030 --> 01:14:43.780
It's Easter and I'm back at the Vatican

01:14:43.780 --> 01:14:46.730
for no other reason than it's
another Easter with the Pope.

01:14:48.230 --> 01:14:50.713
My family no longer expects
me home for Passover.

01:14:53.680 --> 01:14:55.510
I managed to get tickets to what they call

01:14:55.510 --> 01:14:57.183
a private audience with the Pope.

01:14:59.270 --> 01:15:01.370
but It wasn't as private as I imagined it.

01:15:05.850 --> 01:15:08.050
I imagined we'd get to
exchange a few words.

01:15:10.175 --> 01:15:14.092
(fans cheering and applauding)

01:15:20.880 --> 01:15:24.443
But instead, he just passed right by me.

01:15:27.080 --> 01:15:28.230
Leaving barely a trace.

01:15:36.010 --> 01:15:38.470
The truth is, when I stopped looking,

01:15:38.470 --> 01:15:40.470
things began revealing themselves to me.

01:15:42.540 --> 01:15:45.540
Like, later that night when I
stumbled into this little bar,

01:15:47.100 --> 01:15:49.873
and there was Elvis again
in the form of a cover band.

01:15:51.540 --> 01:15:53.740
I'm used to him following
me everywhere now.

01:15:55.630 --> 01:15:56.773
Pope tape 56.

01:15:58.645 --> 01:16:03.645
(♪ I'm all Shook Up ♪)
(audience cheers and applauds)

01:16:14.790 --> 01:16:15.870
Floriana started telling me

01:16:15.870 --> 01:16:18.530
about how she first discovered Elvis,

01:16:18.530 --> 01:16:20.753
and we slipped outside to
hear each other better.

01:16:22.485 --> 01:16:27.152
(Floriana speaking in Italian)

01:17:10.185 --> 01:17:15.018
Then later that night over a
coffee, I almost missed this.

01:17:17.156 --> 01:17:20.223
- Everything comes from
the loneliness and sorrows.

01:17:21.060 --> 01:17:26.060
I think that all human beings
have a big hole in the soul

01:17:26.850 --> 01:17:29.770
and when you felt alone,
you look for something

01:17:31.132 --> 01:17:34.093
that could fill it.

01:17:35.460 --> 01:17:38.883
Probably is strange or is
sad that Elvis could do that,

01:17:38.883 --> 01:17:42.463
I don't know, but I felt
alone and Elvis was there.

01:17:44.352 --> 01:17:46.769
(soft music)

01:18:08.930 --> 01:18:10.100
- [Annie] Photographer Ralph Burns

01:18:10.100 --> 01:18:13.100
has been collecting images
of Elvis even longer.

01:18:13.100 --> 01:18:14.360
Over 40 years.

01:18:14.360 --> 01:18:16.253
- I'm sort of overwhelmed.

01:18:17.490 --> 01:18:19.093
- [Annie] He's become a good friend.

01:18:20.430 --> 01:18:22.870
I asked him if he ever solved the mystery

01:18:22.870 --> 01:18:24.560
and he just smiled and said,

01:18:24.560 --> 01:18:26.360
why do you think I keep coming back?

01:18:27.330 --> 01:18:30.723
- File cabinet drawers full of negatives.

01:18:31.710 --> 01:18:34.500
And many of them I've not
really spent any time with yet

01:18:34.500 --> 01:18:39.040
so I'm actually both looking forward to

01:18:39.040 --> 01:18:40.643
and dreading on another level.

01:18:48.270 --> 01:18:49.650
- [Annie] More than anyone,

01:18:49.650 --> 01:18:50.960
Ralph understands what it's like

01:18:50.960 --> 01:18:53.700
to stay with one subject for so long.

01:18:53.700 --> 01:18:57.053
Still shooting on film,
developing the work by hand.

01:19:02.390 --> 01:19:04.160
To me, his images get closest

01:19:04.160 --> 01:19:06.160
to that unknown thing I've been seeking.

01:19:08.350 --> 01:19:09.300
And I asked him if he'd sit

01:19:09.300 --> 01:19:11.050
and try to put all this into words,

01:19:11.900 --> 01:19:13.850
all the things I've never been able to.

01:19:15.450 --> 01:19:19.770
- I go there looking
for things which to me

01:19:19.770 --> 01:19:22.980
reveal something about all of us.

01:19:22.980 --> 01:19:26.833
How we interrelate with the beyond.

01:19:27.940 --> 01:19:32.100
And I keep going back thinking
I'm going to find an answer

01:19:32.100 --> 01:19:34.470
or that there is some definitive image

01:19:34.470 --> 01:19:35.853
that's gonna sum this up.

01:19:36.992 --> 01:19:40.980
There's never a photograph
that's gonna capture this

01:19:40.980 --> 01:19:44.740
because it's not about the
obvious, it's about the subtle

01:19:44.740 --> 01:19:47.493
and the mysterious and the mystical.

01:19:48.590 --> 01:19:50.290
And maybe I go back for that, too.

01:19:51.410 --> 01:19:56.410
And I've got a deep
appreciation of these fans

01:19:57.820 --> 01:20:01.873
who come year after year
because of a deep abiding,

01:20:02.790 --> 01:20:05.663
now lost love, for another human being.

01:20:06.920 --> 01:20:09.273
- [Annie] A deep abiding, now lost love,

01:20:10.530 --> 01:20:11.730
for another human being.

01:20:12.844 --> 01:20:15.427
♪ Wise men say ♪

01:20:17.520 --> 01:20:19.370
- [Annie] They were human beings too,

01:20:21.090 --> 01:20:22.640
and knew what it meant to love.

01:20:24.610 --> 01:20:25.553
Just listen.

01:20:26.506 --> 01:20:30.756
♪ But I can't help falling in love ♪

01:20:36.027 --> 01:20:38.653
- But it's hard now to see
this as an image of love,

01:20:39.630 --> 01:20:41.023
without seeing loss.

01:20:47.527 --> 01:20:50.360
(uplifting music)

01:20:57.420 --> 01:21:00.410
We watched as the Pope
received a feeding tube,

01:21:00.410 --> 01:21:01.510
could no longer speak.

01:21:02.682 --> 01:21:05.640
(cello playing "Elgar")

01:21:05.640 --> 01:21:09.103
As Elvis retreated from
the day, into the night.

01:21:14.390 --> 01:21:16.883
As Diana desperately sought privacy.

01:21:19.940 --> 01:21:20.813
Their suffering.

01:21:24.300 --> 01:21:25.133
Our guilt.

01:21:33.540 --> 01:21:34.930
We'll never know which images

01:21:34.930 --> 01:21:38.083
flashed before their eyes in
their final moments, if any.

01:21:39.820 --> 01:21:41.663
I have only their last pictures.

01:21:48.050 --> 01:21:51.300
(church bells ringing)

01:22:00.110 --> 01:22:01.873
I came as soon as I heard the news,

01:22:03.470 --> 01:22:04.853
knowing I had to be here.

01:22:08.589 --> 01:22:11.422
(uplifting music)

01:22:21.670 --> 01:22:26.393
And here I am, on the very spot
I stood all those years ago.

01:22:38.450 --> 01:22:42.193
Only this time, he was gone.

01:22:51.589 --> 01:22:54.422
(uplifting music)

01:23:22.240 --> 01:23:23.250
I'm packing to leave

01:23:23.250 --> 01:23:25.623
and watching the funeral again on the TV.

01:23:27.260 --> 01:23:28.660
And it's like it's not over.

01:23:33.410 --> 01:23:36.450
No matter how long I
spent with the Faithful,

01:23:36.450 --> 01:23:37.753
how much I listened,

01:23:39.280 --> 01:23:41.640
I never did quite actually understand them

01:23:43.700 --> 01:23:46.483
until I lost the person who
was that important to me.

01:23:56.920 --> 01:23:58.463
My aunt Nora fell quite ill.

01:24:00.670 --> 01:24:02.080
She suffered for so long.

01:24:04.730 --> 01:24:06.463
Doctors were of little help.

01:24:09.500 --> 01:24:11.543
I called but never visited.

01:24:14.440 --> 01:24:17.140
How hard would it have been
to have gotten on a plane?

01:24:22.380 --> 01:24:24.023
She ended her own suffering.

01:24:26.400 --> 01:24:27.603
Took her own life.

01:24:32.224 --> 01:24:34.391
Now there's nothing to do.

01:24:35.510 --> 01:24:37.680
Nothing but memorialize her in a film.

01:24:47.520 --> 01:24:50.103
("Dance for Cello")

01:24:55.458 --> 01:24:58.750
I learned that even death has no ending.

01:24:58.750 --> 01:25:00.883
That grief never goes away.

01:25:03.480 --> 01:25:05.580
There will always be unanswered questions.

01:25:26.520 --> 01:25:28.533
Elvis tape 125.

01:25:32.550 --> 01:25:34.223
Elvis was only 42.

01:25:38.170 --> 01:25:39.920
Hard to believe now that I am, too.

01:25:45.260 --> 01:25:46.623
My last Elvis Vigil.

01:25:48.920 --> 01:25:50.100
I shot just one tape.

01:25:53.977 --> 01:25:56.810
(uplifting music)

01:26:29.798 --> 01:26:33.298
(moves into lively music)

01:27:00.134 --> 01:27:04.134
(audience cheers and applauds)
